7pm notifying us of an incident involving 12 persons. “It was discovered that it was an uncomplete building under construction that collapsed on the persons. “Some were rescued alive with injuries. All victims taken to Waziri Gidado hospital,” Muhammed however stated. Vanguard News Nigeria. By Bashir Bello A 50-year-old man, identity undisclosed has on Friday drowned in a pond as twelve others survived from a building collapse in Kano State. It was gathered that the incident happened in Nassarawa and Dala Local Government areas of the state respectively. Also read: TRENDING VIDEO: 30 Nigerian… August 21, 2020 In "News" A 15-year-old boy, Mohammed Basa, has drowned while bathing in a pond at Kuka Bulukiya Community in the Dala Local Government Area of Kano State. September 17, 2018 In "Metro" A 40-year-old man, Mohammed Mohammed, has drowned while bathing in a pond at Kwanar Tattarawa in Dawakin Tofa Local Government Area of Kano State. October 22, 2019 In "News"